                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1013: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-06T09:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1933—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. My telegram No. 7, February 5, 11 a.m. If language Haitian Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs proposes to use in his reply to Peruvian Government is not
                    satisfactory could Department let me know at once together with suggestions as
                    to changes in order that I may communicate with Foreign Minister before his
                    message is sent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
